FBIS4-5124 "dreas067_i_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 Cambodia Fighting North of Pailin on 5 Apr Reported Fighting North of Pailin on 5 Apr Reported BK0704074094 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 6 Apr 94 BK0704074094 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Cambodian BFN [Text] A regiment of the invading troops of the communist Vietnamese puppets and the two-headed government -- backed by five tanks, artillery, and multiple rocket batteries -- launched an attack on 5 April to break through our forces surrounding them in Sala Krau. The enemy was completely routed. Here is the preliminary result: We killed 15 soldiers and wounded a large number. Furthermore, we smashed and killed nine division and regimental officers, including a deputy to Prum Moranak, a tank commander, and three infantry commanders. We seized some weapons and war materiel.
